    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third party that holds the money and documents until the sale is complete, ensuring both buyer and seller meet their obligations. It's a security measure to protect both parties from fraud, ensuring that the buyer doesn't pay until they've inspected the property and the seller doesn't receive the final payment until the house is theirs. In Toronto, it's a legal requirement to have an escrow account when closing on a house to safeguard the transaction.",
