      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money in escrow is held in a secure account by the title insurance company, and it's not just sitting there. Throughout the escrow period, the funds are used to pay off the seller's mortgage, settle any outstanding liens or taxes, and cover any other closing costs as agreed upon in your purchase contract. The title insurance company acts as a gatekeeper, ensuring that all parties are fulfilling their obligations before releasing the funds to the rightful owner. It's a safeguard in place to protect your investment and ensure a smooth transfer of ownership.",
